OL,3,CInside the Birmingham school
OL,4,Csupporting displaced children
OL,6,FDiana Sutton, Director at the Bell
OL,7,FFoundation, said evidence suggests
OL,8,Fsome schools don't want to take EAL
OL,9,Fchildren because they fear they won't
OL,10,Fbe able to properly support them or
OL,11,Fthat it will have a negative impact on
OL,12,Fthe school's results.
OL,14,FMultilingual classrooms are becoming
OL,15,Fthe norm, yet experts warn that
OL,16,Fteachers feel unsupported and
OL,17,Funprepared due to funding cuts.
OL,19,FUnstable accommodation for displaced
OL,20,Fchildren is also a barrier to learning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/20
