OL,6,FFor primary schools, they will receive
OL,7,F#610 per pupil for three years, while
OL,8,Fsecondary schools receive #1,630 per
OL,9,Fpupil for the same period.
OL,11,FThat can be spent on things like
OL,12,Ftranslators, for example, but it's not
OL,13,Fring-fenced, and schools only receive
OL,14,Fthat funding for those registered at
OL,15,Fthe start of the academic year, based
OL,16,Fon the October census.
OL,18,FThat means any child who arrives mid-
OL,19,Fterm will not benefit from any
OL,20,Fadditional funds, often leaving the
OL,21,Fschool to front the costs.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/20
